column5: Rick (manitoubass2) asked me for some unedited video footage, footage that shows a real "behind the scenes" look at what goes on during my trips. Nothing scripted, just the true reality.  My group and I returned from Mojikit Lake north of Armstrong late last night, so I present to you a short glimpse of camp life...   Warning - some salty language!
Ohhhh my sides are killing me mike!  Video of the year!  G

Hahahahahahaha  Its a walleye rodeo!!!  Your vids are indeed epic but that sir had me in stitches????  Well played?  Indeed the credit goes to mike and crew but OFC yall better thank me for requesting this??  Hahaha in still laughing 10 minutes later
Hahaha, awesome video. I hope that bait caster made it back to the boat!

Ohhhh my sides are killing me mike!  Video of the year!  G  Glad you like it bud LOL!  Hahahahahahaha  Its a walleye rodeo!!!  Your vids are indeed epic but that sir had me in stitches  Well played  Indeed the credit goes to mike and crew but OFC yall better thank me for requesting this  Hahaha in still laughing 10 minutes later Hey what can I say Rick, you inspired me.  Hahaha, awesome video. I hope that bait caster made it back to the boat! Thanks, and yes the rod/reel was retrieved.

video of videos, lmao,  laughing so much almost forgot to breathe.
